Here is a TekAutomate Steps UI flow to connect to your MSO4/5/6 Series oscilloscope, save the CH1 waveform to a binary file, and then disconnect.

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "label": "Connect to Oscilloscope",
      "params": {
        "instrumentIds": [],
        "printIdn": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "save_waveform",
      "label": "Save CH1 Waveform to File",
      "params": {
        "source": "CH1",
        "filename": "ch1.bin",
        "format": "bin"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "label": "Disconnect from Oscilloscope",
      "params": {
        "instrumentIds": []
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

You can change the filename or format (bin, csv, wfm, mat) as needed.

